<TITLE> Opposition walks out twice </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 24 (bdnews24.com)  The BNP-led opposition staged two walkouts from parliament Tuesday, alleging violation of the rules of procedure in passing bills, a day after it went back to the House after 26 days. The opposition MPs walked of the House just before Maghrib prayers as the speaker overruled a rule of procedure that gave MPs three days to submit notices on bills for adoption in the House. They returned at 7.00 pm after Maghrib recess, only to walk out again an hour later as the speaker upheld his decision on withholding the Rule 77. Ruling party MPs Suranjit Sengupta and Tofail Ahmed, among others, argued with BNP's Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury who termed the speaker's decision "against rules of procedure". bdn
